title: DZ Trees - Conifers (Pines, Cypresses and Firs)
description: 60 high-quality coniferous trees/cypresses. Highres Nanite models and textures of six different tree species, ten trees of each species. Efficient and highly user-friendly materials and material instances with versatile and high-performance wind effects.
longDescription:
Be sure to check out our other products


Possible PERFORMANCE BOOSTERS when using VSM (virtual shadow maps):

1. Adjust "Anti-Aliasing Method" in "Project Settings" to "TAA" instead of "TSR".

2. Adjust "Engine Scalability Settings" to "High" or "Medium".

3. Adjust "World Position Offset Disable Distance" of all the DZ tree meshes in your level to be the same value as wind kill distance (e.g. 10000 = 100m) in master materials.

4. Adjust "Shadow Cache invalidation behavior" of all the DZ tree meshes in your level to "Rigid" or "Static".

With these 60 trees, you can create impressive environments and conifer forests from all around the world. Lower trunks have been displaced based on bark height map textures. Shaping the trunk based on the height/displacement maps is an alternative method to photogrammetry, and it does not compromise the resolution/accuracy of the bark textures. Professionally made tree models, textures and materials ensure that the quality is in line with the best assets in the Market Place.


Full Nanite support:

All the trees are high-res Nanite meshes and are using Nanite by default. Everything is optimized to achieve the best performance without compromising quality.


Full Lumen support:

This product supports Lumen in all the supported engine versions mentioned in the beginning of this product page (UE 5.1 and above). Lumen can be activated in "Project Settings" => "Rendering" => "Global Illumination" => "Dynamic Global Illumination Method" => "Lumen". More information about Lumen can be found in Unreal Engine 5.0 documentation.


Efficient and highly user-friendly materials:

Master materials (2 pieces) are very easy to understand and effective. Material instances created from them allow easy customization of trees and wind effects according to your wishes. Wind effects are very cheap for PC performance, yet very realistic. Watch the tutorial videos to get an idea of all the useful features that these versatile materials offer. These include, for example, blending two bark textures using vertex color, using snow and wetness effects, possibility to add moss/lichen and peeled bark to trunks and branches, adjusting the visibility of leaves/needles, killing the wind effect smoothly according to the distance and mixing different wind directions with different strengths. Wind effects also use two vertex colors to get branches move more naturally.


DZ Trees - Conifers features:

Made for Unreal Engine 5.1 and above

High resolution Nanite meshes for trees (60 pieces)

High resolution textures

Wind system (recommended to use MPC, only needs to adjust one number to give wind strength for all the trees)

Snow effect (recommended to be adjusted mostly in master material instances, 2 pieces)

Wetness Effect (recommended to be adjusted mostly in master material instances, 2 pieces)

Possibility to add moss/lichen and peeled bark to trunks and branches

It's recommended to have an RTX GPU, at least an RTX 2080. Demo videos were recorded in 4K with an RTX 3080 GPU.
